      },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Can I scan MCP servers for security vulnerabilities before installing them?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'Yes. snyk/agent-scan (AgentRank score 82.28, 1,907 stars) is purpose-built to scan MCP servers, AI agents, and agent skills for security findings. cisco-ai-defense/mcp-scanner (73.73, 843 stars) from Cisco scans MCP servers for threats. Both are open source and can be run before deploying any third-party MCP server.',
      },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'What are the biggest security risks with MCP servers?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'The main risks are: (1) Prompt injection — a malicious MCP server could try to hijack your agent through tool responses. (2) Excessive permissions — servers that request write access when they only need read. (3) Supply chain compromise — abandoned or low-maintenance servers may have unpatched vulnerabilities. (4) Secrets exfiltration — servers with filesystem or network access could leak API keys or credentials. (5) Tool poisoning — servers that execute different code than documented.',
      },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'What does an AgentRank score tell me about MCP server security?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
